```
If the last digit is ```9```, we remove that ```9``` from the vector and add ```1``` to the vector without ```9```; essentially carrying the ```1```. After adding the ```1``` we put``` 0``` at the end of the vector, which will take the place of the ```9 ```from this particular recursion. Since the input is described as non-empty, we can assume the vector will only be empty if it was composed solely of 9's. Thus, we simply push_back ```1``` and return the vector.
This allows for ```plusOne([9,9,9])``` to return ```[1,0,0,0]```

