# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
- This concept is great, and we can imagine it well enough.
- We always add the number to another at the end, Ex: 1002 + 2 = 100***4*** 
- If we get any carry we pass it to the next number from right to left.
- Similarly it's an easy version of that.
##### Let's dive deep into it:
- We have to just add 1 to the number whose digit are represented in array format.
###### - There can be only two cases:
1. The number = 9 (need to pass one as carry, and number will be equals to zero)
2. If number !=9 , number++;

###### - The Special Case:
1. Let's say the number is in form of 999, after adding 1, number= 1000 (**Need to increase the size of vector**: (v.push_back(0))
2. If not then come out of loop.


# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
- Iterate over the vector: 
 1. if i==n-1, v[i]++
 2. then check if v[i]==10
  - v[i]=0
  - if(i!=0) v[i-1]++
  - else push_back 0, and v[i]=1; 

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
