solutions.content:
If the last digit is any number from **0-8**, incrementing that by 1 will not cause any issue, making the case simple. In case the last digit is **9**, adding 1 will make it 10, so 9 will be replaced by 0 and addition of 1 to the previous number is to be done.

Consider the example of 99 = [9,9] - adding 1 to last digit makes it 0 and 1 is added to previous digit and that again will become 0. Now since this is the first digit of the number (here in list format), 1 needs to be appended before it to finish the addition. This is done in the code blow. 

```
def plusOne(self, digits: List[int]) -> List[int]:
        n = len(digits)

        while n>0:
            if digits[n-1]==9:
                if (n-1) == 0:
                    digits[n-1] = 0
                    temp = [1] + digits
                    return temp
                else:
                    digits[n-1] = 0
                    n = n-1
            else:
                digits[n-1] += 1
                return digits

        return digits
```

