# Intuition
To not use Brute Force Approach and optimize the solution.
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
* for numbers less than or equal to 8 - can directly be incremented by 1.
* eg: 786 + 1= 787
* for number which is equal to 9 - will be replaced with 0 and generate a carry
* That carry will be further added to the beginning. 
* eg: 9 + 1 = 0 carry generated  
* Now 1 will be placed in the beginning. 
* Final array will be 10 

<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity:O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity:O(1)
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> plusOne(vector<int>& digits) {
        short i =0; // for smaller integers
        bool carry =0; // carry can be zero or one so used bool
        for(i=digits.size()-1;i>=0;--i){
            if(digits[i]<=8){ // for digits less than 8
                digits[i]++; // incremented by 1 directly
                carry =0; // no need of carry
                break; // increased the number by 1 and break
            }
            else{
                digits[i]=0; // else if the number is 9 , so replace the number by 0
                carry=1; // generate a carry 1
            }
        }
        if (carry) digits.insert(digits.begin(),1); // as number was increased by 1 there was 1 carry , carry will be placed in beginning 
        return digits; // return the incremented digits as final output 
    }
int main(){
    return 0;
}
};
```

