# Intuition


# Approach
Here,First we have to take two cases
1) if digit < 9
    casually increment digit[i];
2) if digit == 9
    here we find no of last occuring 9's so,we increment just      before index of first 9 in given array order.
->apply for loop to get incrementing position
two cases
 1.if only one 9 i.e., {9} then we have update 9 to 1 and pushback 0;
 2. if no of 9's > 1 (ex:499,87999)then we update the just before index of first consecutive 9 and update the remaining values 0f 9with for loop by 0



# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)

- Space complexity: O(1)


# Code
```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<int> plusOne(vector<int>& digits) {
        int n = digits.size();
        #for storing last consecutive 9's location appearing from reverse
        int a = 0;

        if(digits[n-1] < 9){
            digits[n-1]++;
            return digits;
        }

        if(digits[n-1]==9){
            #for finding last consective 9 from reverse
            for(int i = n-1; i>=0;i--){

                if(digits[i] == 9){
                    a  =  i;                 
                }
                else if(digits[i]<9){
                    break;

                }

            }
            #updating 9's with 1
            if(a == 0){
                digits[0] = 1;
                for(int i = 1;i<n;i++){
                    digits[i] = 0;
                }
                digits.push_back(0);
            }
            #updating 9's with 0
            if(a>0){
                 digits[a-1]++;
                for(int i = a; i<n; i++){
                    digits[i] = 0;
                }
            }   
        }

      return digits;
    }

};

```


