solutions.content:
* iterate through S1 again and again, track the pointer position of S2 at the end of each S1 iteration
* continue until the S2 pointer comes back to previous position, which means we've found a cycle
	* break up into 3 parts: pre-cycle, in-cycle, post-cycle
		* calculate loop count for the in-cycle part
		* snitch pre-cycle and post-cycle together, and calculate the loop count for this combined parts
```
class Solution {
    public int getMaxRepetitions(String s1, int n1, String s2, int n2) {
        int nn1 = s1.length();
        int nn2 = s2.length();

        int[][] records = new int[2][n1+1];
