# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We cannot actually store (s1 * n1) and (s2 * n2) due to memory constraints. Therefore we need to make n1 loops over s1, and for every n2 matches of s2 that we can find we increment count by 1.

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(n1 * s1.Length)

- Space complexity:
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
O(1)

# Code
```
public class Solution {
    public int GetMaxRepetitions(string s1, int n1, string s2, int n2) {
        int count = 0, ind = 0, loops = 0;
        for (int i = 0; i < n1; i++){
            for (int k = 0; k < s1.Length; k++){
                if (s1[k] == s2[ind]) ind++;
                if (ind == s2.Length){
                    ind = 0;
                    loops++;
                }
                if (loops == n2){
                    loops = 0;
                    count++;
                }
            }
            if (ind == 0 && loops == 0){
                int add = count;
                int times = i + 1;
                while (i + times < n1){
                    i += times;
                    count += add;
                }
            }
        }

        return count;
    }
}
```

