solutions.content:
Firstly we calculate the **counts** array which is number of s1 required to contain 1,2,3,4,... s2s.  For each character in s2, we greedily identify the next matching character in s1 in circular fashion. We keep track of the offset of s2[0] in s1 and remember the firs time an offset is used the second time and stop when an offset is used the third time. This way we obtain sufficient data to know that the initial [s1,b] contains [s2,idx], then every [s1,q] contains [s2, p]. The complexity is O(L^2) where L is the length of s1 and s2. The result counts array is O(L) length.

The we use binary search in **getNumberOfS2n2** to identify number of [s2,n2] that fit in [s1,n1]. The function **getNumS1ForS2k** calculates number of s1 required to hold [s2,k].

```
  public static int getMaxRepetitions(String s1, int n1, String s2, int n2) {
    if (n1 == 0 || n2 == 0) {
      return 0;
    }
    // If s2 contain any character not appear in s1, return 0.
    for (char c : s2.toCharArray()) {
      if (s1.indexOf(c) < 0) {
        return 0;
      }
    }

    List<Integer> counts = calculateCounts(s1, s2);
    return getNumberOfS2n2(n1, n2, counts);
  }

  // Calculate counts array in which counts[i] is the number of s1 required to contain [s2,i].
  // The special counts[0] hold the index when first observation of repeat offset.
  // We stop when observe the start offset the third time. For examples:
  //   1. cba abc => 1,3,5
  //   2. acb ab => 1,1,2
  //   3. aaa aa => 3,1,2,2,3,4,4
  //   4. baba baab => 2,2,3,5,6
  //   5. bacaba abacab => 2,2,3,4
  //   6. niconiconi nico => 3,1,1,2,2,3
  static List<Integer> calculateCounts(String s1, String s2) {
    int m = s1.length();
    int n = s2.length();
    List<Integer> counts = new ArrayList<>();
    counts.add(0);

    int nums1 = 0;
    // Map from index in s1 of the first character of s2 to number of times such index is seen.
    Map<Integer, Integer> seen = new HashMap<>();
    int j = m-1;
    while (true) {
      for (int i = 0; i < n; i++) {
        if (j == m-1) {
