solutions.content:
**Time Complexity:** O(m x n), where m is no of rows, n is no of columns in inital matrix
**Space Complexity:** O(1)

**Intution:** Consider a 2D matrix arr of size m x n, and a counter, let's say **t** to count the elements linearly and using it we can visualise this 2D matrix as 1D matrix. Now to convert it back to 2D matrix (which will be the solution) we can use this formula:

**arr[i][j]** = **arr[t/no_of_columns][t%no_of_columns]**, where i, j points to particular valid index

and it will map to the required index in the solution matirx. Try with 3-4 2D matrix of different sizes and it will become more clear.


```
class Solution {
public:
    vector<vector<int>> matrixReshape(vector<vector<int>>& mat, int r, int c) {
//      count of rows & columns of initial matrix 
        int m = mat.size(), n = mat[0].size();

//      Checking if matrix can be reshaped or not
        if ((m*n) != (r*c)) return mat;

//      pointer to insert values in the new / reshaped matrix
        int t = 0;

//      vector to store the new matrix
        vector<vector<int>> res(r, vector<int> (c)); 

        for(int i = 0; i < m; i++){
            for(int j = 0; j < n; j++){
                res[t/c][t%c] = mat[i][j];
                t++;
            }
        }
        return res;
    }
};
```

