Here, we create a new matrix with size r*c, and we create two variables, k (row) and l (coloum), for iterating in the matrix. Here, we also need to check if the l reach the last element of the first row, in which case we need to initialise l with 0 to indicate the first coloum and increment k++ to indicate the second raw so that this type of logic can easily create new matrix.


