# Intuition
KCE

# Approach
1. Check whether the given matrix size(m,n) and wanted reshaped matrix size (r,c) equal or  not,  (m * n==r * c).
2. If equal first create one Array and pass the values of given matrix.
3. Next create another matrix with wanted shape and size using given rows and column.
4. Now pass the stored array elements to new reshaped matrix. 
5.  If not equal return a same matrix given in a question.

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n^2)

- Space complexity:
O(n)

# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int[][] matrixReshape(int[][] a, int r, int c) {
        int m=a.length;
        int n=a[0].length;
        if(m*n==r*c)
        {
               int p[]=new int[r*c];
               int k=0;
              for(int i=0;i<m;i++){
               for(int j=0;j<n;j++){
                p[k++]=a[i][j];
               }
              }
             int q=0;

             int b[][]=new int[r][c];
            for(int i=0;i<r;i++){
              for(int j=0;j<c;j++){
                  b[i][j]=p[q++];
              }
            }
            return b;
     }
    else
    return a;
    }
}
```

