# Intuition
Pattern for first k position is { n , arr[i-1]-(n-i) , arr[i-1]+(n-i) , arr[i-1]-(n-i)......... and so on }

Pattern after k postion is (arr[i-1] +/- 1) , depending whether the last position was a addition or subtraction

# Complexity
- Time complexity:
O(n)
- Space complexity:
O(n)
# Code
```
class Solution {
    public int[] constructArray(int n, int k) {

        int num=-1;
        int[] res = new int[n];
        res[0]=n;
        for(int i=1;i<n;i++){
            if(i<k){
                if(num>0){    
                    res[i]=res[i-1]+(n-i);
                    num*=-1;
                }else{
                    res[i]=res[i-1]-(n-i);
                    num*=-1;
                }
            }else{
                res[i]=res[i-1]+num;
            }
        }

        return res;

    }
}
