The sign flips each time until 0, and afterward, all the difference between two adjacent items could be 1, that is ans[i] = i+1. Here comes the code:
```
class Solution {
    public int[] constructArray(int n, int k) {
        int[] ans = new int[n];
        ans[0] = 1;
        int v = k;
        int sign = 1;
        for(int i = 1; i < n; i++) {
            if(k == 1 || v == 0){
                ans[i] = i+1;
                continue;
            }          
            ans[i] = ans[i-1] + v*sign;
            v--;
            sign = -sign;
        }
        return ans;
    }
}
