# Intuition
If you look at the pattern of various output values (different n & k values), you will find that we always start with initial value 1 and keep addition and subtracting decreasing value of k from initial value. And where ever possible, always choose lower value if that is not already selected before. E.g. for n = 10, k = 7 
Start with initial value of 1, the follow this to populate solution matrix:
1 + 7 = 8
8 - 6 = 2
2 + 5 = 7
7 - 4 = 3
3 + 3 = 6
6 - 2 = 4
4 + 1 = 5
And then just append rest of the remaning non-explored no's at the end.


