solutions.content:
*  First we take the count of every character in the string and store it in a unordered map.We use unordered map because it is time effiecient.
*  Then we create a max heap of type " pair<int,char> " ,.We use a max heap here because we want to get finished with the highest no. of characters available first.
*  So we take out the first two elements in the heap and insert one character from each in our ans string and reduce count of 1 from both.
*    We then insert the elements back if the count is >0 otherwise inserting won't be of any use to us.
*    We only do the above process till the max heap size become one.
*    Once it becomes 1 we come out of it.Then check if the last char present has a count >1 if it has so we have no choice but to return "" else insert the last character and return ans. 
```
class Solution {
public:
    string reorganizeString(string s) {
        unordered_map<char,int> m;
        for(char c:s){
            m[c]++;
        }
        priority_queue<pair<int,char>> maxh;
        for(auto itr:m){
            maxh.push({itr.second,itr.first});
        }
        string ans="";
        while(maxh.size()>1){
            auto [a,b]=maxh.top();
            maxh.pop();
            auto [c,d]=maxh.top();
            maxh.pop();
            ans.push_back(b);
            ans.push_back(d);
            a--;
            c--;
            if(a>0){
                maxh.push({a,b});
            }
            if(c>0){
                maxh.push({c,d});
            }
        }
        if(maxh.size()==1){
            auto [a,b]=maxh.top();
            maxh.pop();
            if(a>1)return "";
            ans.push_back(b);
        }
        return ans;
    }
};
```

