The idea and intuition of the solution is as follows:
1. Count the occurences of each alphabet in the given string
2. Construct a Max heap with (count, alphabet) as elements
3. Now, pop two elements each time (two maximum occuring elements) and add them to the answer (include the edge cases when heap is empty after one pop)
4. This approach works because the best way to construct the solution string is to greedily select the maximum occuring element so that they get finished alternatively.

Note: Code is not that much clean but it is short I guess😅

```
