solutions.content:
**The idea is to pick up two most frequent elements and add the to the resultant string alternate wise, till the character with lesser count is exhausted. And the latter, is added to the heap again if its count is greater than 0. This is repeated till we have <=1 elements in heap.**

```
string reorganizeString(string S) {
        map<char,int> mp;
        int n=S.length();
        for(int i=0;i<n;i++) //taking count of each character
            mp[S[i]]++;
        priority_queue<pair<int,char>> hp;

        for(auto i=mp.begin();i!=mp.end();i++){ //pushing elements to the heap, with its frequency as 1st element and character as second
            hp.push({i->second,i->first});
        }
        string s; // s stores the resultant string

        while(hp.size()>=2){// implementation of above mentioned idea
            pair<int,char> a=hp.top();
            hp.pop();
            pair<int,char>b=hp.top();
            hp.pop();
            while((b.first)>0){
                s.push_back(a.second);
                s.push_back(b.second);
                b.first--;
                a.first--;

            }
            if(a.first>0)
                hp.push(a);
        }
        if(hp.empty()) // if heap is empty, simply return it
            return s;

        if(hp.top().first>1) // it means we have one character, which has still count >=2, if now added there's no way to have any character between them
            return "";// so return empty string
        else if(hp.top().first==1) // if one character is left, simply add it to string
            s.push_back(hp.top().second);
        return s;
    }
