solutions.content:
The idea is straightforward:
1. Get frequencies `f[26]` of chars in `s`. Note if `max > (n+1)/2`, cannot build answer (*early termination check*).
1. Rearrange `s` in sorted frequencies.
1. Build answer string by taking chars from rearranged `s` in round robin way (each small string has no duplicated chars).
1. Join small strings to get answer.

```cpp
    string reorganizeString(string s) 
    {
        // build frequency of chars
        vector<int> f(26);
        for (char c : s) ++f[c-'a'];
        int maxFre = *max_element(f.begin(), f.end()), n = s.size(); 
        if (maxFre > (n+1)/2) return ""; // early termination

        // sort frequencies
        set<pair<int,int>> sf;
        for (int i = 0; i < f.size(); ++i) sf.emplace(f[i], i); // (count, char)

        // sort chars by sorted frequencies
        for (auto& x : sf) s.replace(n-=x.first, x.first, x.first, 'a'+x.second);

        // build answer by round robin
        vector<string> strs(maxFre);
        while (n < s.size()) strs[n++%maxFre] += s[n]; // round robin
        return accumulate(strs.begin(), strs.end(), s="");
