# Intuition
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->
We Just need to use the logic of keeping a Gap between any 2 same characters!! 

# Approach
<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->
Now the same characters can be easily separated keeping a gap of 1 between them or always keeping them at Alternate positions.
So we will simply always pick the characters with the highest frequency and will keep them on alternate position.
The String will be returned empty only when :
1) Length of String is Odd :    
"aaabb" => "ababa"(pssbl)
"aaaab" => not pssbl
That is if any character occurs more than (len+1)/2, then return the empty string
2) Length of String is Even :    
"aaabbb" => "ababab"
"aaaabb" => not pssbl
If any character occurs more than half the length of the string 

Conclusion : Ans is empty string only if any character occurs more than (len+1)/2
{len denotes length of the string}

# Complexity
- Time complexity: $$O(n*log(n))$$
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: $$O(26)$$
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

# Code
```
#define ll int
class Solution {
public:
    string reorganizeString(string s) {
        int sz = s.size();
        vector<int> v(26,0);
        for(int i = 0;i<sz;++i){
            v[s[i]-'a']++;
            if(v[s[i]-'a'] > (sz+1)/2){return "";}
        }
        map<char,ll> mp;
        for(int i = 0;i<26;++i){
            if(v[i]){
                mp[i+'a'] = v[i];
            }
        }

        multiset<pair<ll,char>> ms;
        for(auto it:mp){
            ms.insert({it.second,it.first});
        }

        string tmp;
        while(!ms.empty()){
            auto p = *ms.rbegin();ms.erase(p);
            while(p.first--){
                tmp += p.second;
            }
        }
        s.clear();s = tmp;

        vector<char> ok(sz);
        int i = 0,j = 0,n = sz;
        while(n--){   
            ok[i] = s[j];
            i += 2;++j;
            if(i >= sz){
                i = 1;
            }
        }
        string ans;
        for(auto it:ok){ans += it;}
        return ans;
    }
};
```

