This is def. a little tricky one!
 What we planning to do here is, everytime we add that character to the ```ans``` string, which PRESENTLY is the **most abundant one**!
so for that we use *hash table* to store the freq. of occurence of each character and then use a *max-heap* to arrange those frequencies along with its respective character such that the character with highest freq. of occurence appears on top! (property of max-heap)

Now, one by one we get the **1st most abundant** char from max-heap and append it to the ```ans``` string, then we get the **2nd most abundant** char and append it to the ```ans``` string. We do this so that there is no chances of repeating of same characters.

Please look at the code for line by line explanation!
