# Intuition
We start by identifying the character with the maximum frequency and store its index. If this maximum frequency is greater than half the length of the input string, a valid reorganization isn't possible, and an empty string is returned. Otherwise, we construct the reorganized string by alternating between inserting the character with the maximum frequency (ensuring no adjacent duplicates) and distributing the remaining characters. By following this alternating insertion pattern, we create a reorganized string that meets the specified criteria of non-adjacent identical characters.
<!-- Describe your first thoughts on how to solve this problem. -->

# Approach
STEPS:
- We iterate through the input string s and populate the count vector based on the frequency of each character.

- We then find the character with the maximum count (frequency) and stores its index in the variable letter.

- If the maximum count is greater than half the length of the input string (meaning it's not possible to reorganize the string without adjacent identical characters), we return an empty string.

- Otherwise, we initialize a string ans with the same content as the input string s.

- We then start reorganizing the characters in the string ans. First we fill the characters with the character having the maximum count, ensuring that no two adjacent characters are the same. We do this by inserting the character at every second index, starting from index 0.

- After using up the characters with the maximum count, we proceed to fill the remaining characters with the remaining characters based on their counts, again ensuring that no two adjacent characters are the same. We do this by continuing to insert characters at every second index.

<!-- Describe your approach to solving the problem. -->

# Complexity
- Time complexity: O(n)
<!-- Add your time complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->

- Space complexity: O(k) where k is the total unique characters in the string
<!-- Add your space complexity here, e.g. $$O(n)$$ -->
UPVOTE. Glad to help.
